If you are trying to set a content property using the REST API you need to send that describes the content property such as:

{code}
{
    "key": "example-property-key",
    "value": {
        "anything": "goes"
    }
}
{code}

If you don't specify the "value" field or you name it incorrectly, you get a NullPointerException.  We should handle this case with better validation.

